{
  "stem": "19218.5",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 98,
      "text": "I know the kids miss her also.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 99,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] Terribly.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 100,
      "text": "And my friends.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 101,
      "text": "I got-- I have really wonderful kids.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 102,
      "text": "And you'll meet 'em.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 103,
      "text": "[SIGHS] And I also have wonderful, wonderful friends.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 104,
      "text": "And nieces and nephews, which without them, I don't think I could have made it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 105,
      "text": "My friends were constantly on-- on my case.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 106,
      "text": "I mean, they would never leave me alone.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 107,
      "text": "My nieces and nephews, especially-- Karen and [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 108,
      "text": "Sid. ?] And their children, just like our children.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 109,
      "text": "I mean, they-- they-- they just grew up with us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 110,
      "text": "And-- and-- and-- and-- and-- and it's not just them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 111,
      "text": "But it still continued.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 112,
      "text": "I mean, it's-- it's-- it's her nephew.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 113,
      "text": "And it's from her side of the family.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 114,
      "text": "Without them, I would have been much more-- harder for me to go on.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 115,
      "text": "And they still the same, even now.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 116,
      "text": "I mean, it hasn't stopped just because she's gone.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 117,
      "text": "It's still the same, so-- thank god for great family.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 118,
      "text": "And same thing goes with my kids, of course.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, for my own-- [SIGHS] you know, we-- we, the survivors-- I'm speaking about myself and maybe I'm speaking for the other ones who are not here anymore.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We never talked, or we were not ashamed-- afraid to talk-- because we just couldn't believe what we went through.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We couldn't believe it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So how could we make someone else-- other people believe it?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I mean, seeing children just taken by the legs and torn apart.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Taken by the legs, hit against brick walls.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Gassing people, shooting people in front of you.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I-- I mean, who would believe it?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Mass graves, I mean, with-- with thousands of people in one.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I worked in that last camp.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I used to put them into that grave and just put a little lime over them.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
